         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">19/1/87 ¶  ¶ Let me thank you, dear Professor Bocage, for your kind note and for all your friendliness. ¶  Would it not be possible to obtain some actual  ¶ documents ¶  in the  ¶ Archives ¶  of Lisbo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.01.19a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To José Barbosa du Bocage </p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Arquivo Histórico do Museu Bocage, Universidade de Lisboa, Lisbon.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">19/1/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me thank you, dear Professor Bocage, for your kind note and for all your friendliness.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> Would it not be possible to obtain some actual <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">documents</hi>
               </seg> in the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Archives</hi>
               </seg> of Lisbon, concerning the first discovery of the west-coast of Australia by Portuguese Navigators? In all probability some manuscripts, decrees, instructions, rapports &amp;c may still be found.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Barbosa du Bocage, 20 October 1886 (in this edition as 86-10-20a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I now send you a large set of photograms of New Zealand, which shows the magnificent scenery and the changes also, which in some instances the volcanic eruptions have lately made. If you think it <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">proper</hi>
               </seg>, I should be glad, if you would present this to the young Crown Prince. I have two new volumes, one with 76 plates,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B86.08.05 (which included 74 plates)?</p>
               </note> and one with 60 plates (quarto)<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B87.13.04?</p>
               </note> to send soon to the Royal Library at the Palace in continuation of my works.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I hope, soon to forward to you an other zoologic consignment.</p>
         </div>
